node.text: This Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month, we’re sharing some #Perspectives from our athletes and employees. Team athletes Nina Williams (@sheneenagins) and Ashima Shiraishi (@ashimashiraishi) covering climbing, today’s political climate, and what it means to be AAPI in the outdoors. Hosted by Hannah Abuzaineh (@my_name_is_hj ), Senior Manager of Social Impact & The Explore Fund at The North Face.

node.title: AAPI Heritage Month with Nina and Ashima

node.text:
We’ve teamed up with @sonos @sonosradio to launch the Never Stop Exploring station, an immersive outdoor audio experience bringing the sounds of the wild into your home.
 
Never Stop Exploring transports you to nine natural wonders across five continents, from El Capitan in Yosemite to the tallest waterfall in Japan, guided by the first hand experiences of our athletes. You’ll also enjoy original music by Wilco’s @mikaeljorgensen who worked closely with the athletes to incorporate the locations in sound and spirit, creating a one-of-a-kind series of environmental compositions. 

Listen on Sonos Radio and link in bio. #NeverStopExploring
📸 @dylangordon
